About
A true landmark for almost 50 years, the family-owned Ellis Island Hotel, Casino & Brewery is an affordable, comfortable blend of casino thrills, family-friendly atmosphere and superb dining with a whole lot of warmth and hospitality. Step through our doors and find yourself face-to-face with an abundance of ways to play. Enjoy our casino with nearly 300 of the hottest slots, live blackjack, roulette, craps and our sports book. Enjoy Las Vegas' #1 Karaoke venue or our very own Ellis Island Brewery, which became the number one brewery in all of Nevada by serving over a million frosty glasses of happiness a year. Eat at our world famous Village Pub Cafe and for a quick bite try Julio's Tacos or Metro Pizza. And yet, despite all of our unique amenities, it is our friendly and personalized service that ranks Ellis Island Hotel, Casino & Brewery among the best in Las Vegas.

  • TravelingSoccerLoon
    Saint Paul, Minnesota6,326 contributions
    Fun Casino That Tries to Provide an Enjoyable Experience with Good Value
    Located just off The Strip, this is a very different experience than visiting most casinos in Vegas especially those on The Strip. It is a more down to earth experience. Smaller and nothing stylish about it but it is clean and still a really fun atmosphere inside. You won't find any $5 minimum blackjack tables on The Strip. The Front Yard offers very good quality food at reasonable prices with indoor and outdoor dining and a nice beer selection. There are a lot of cheap and sketchy places to gamble in town, but I get the sense that the owners are all about providing an enjoyable experience with good value. If I'm going to lose my money to a casino in Vegas, I would rather do it in a place like this that at least tries to offer you something in return for your business.

  • Butch R
    Ravenswood, West Virginia345 contributions
    Ellis Island change
    Since finding this hole in the wall casino, we have made this our go to for breakfast every morning when we are in Las Vegas. First, we would walk from Bally's then we started Ubering from where we were staying. This time we had rented a vehicle and had my family with kids here. The breakfast is always our favorite. The breakfast special has been the go-to selection. It started out in 2012 at $5.99. Steak, egg, potatoes, and toast. Along with coffee, made for a big breakfast deal. It was $12.99 this trip. I guess inflation has hit. The Casino has become a really nice attraction as the facade has expanded and several inside games and slots have made a big move up. They are still expanding I'd say due to the Grand Prix experience last year. I feel this is afforded a transformation to this place. I'm happy for them but am amiss as to my experience with all that is taking place. We like this place due to its old Vegas appeal it had. Table games are now infringing on the slots room, along with the Front Yard bar and grill. This past trip has left me with the feeling that we are losing our Las Vegas experience with Ellis Island. Prices on everything in Vegas has grown to curtail our experiences there. As far as going back, we may go less often and maybe experience this gem less often.
